26, a kids smartwatch is not just an accessory Рђћ it is a <strong>safety device</strong>. The GPS tracker lets parents monitor their child\'s location in real time, while the SOS button connects to parents with a single press in emergencies.</p>\r\n<p>Unlike a phone, a smartwatch <strong>has no internet browser or social media</strong> Рђћ the child can only make calls, use SOS, and send voice messages. This gives parents peace of mind.</p>\r\n</section>\r\n\r\n<section>\r\n<h2>Key Criteria for Choosing</h2>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3>1. GPS Tracking</h3>\r\n<p>Every quality kids watch uses <strong>GPS + LBS + Wi-Fi</strong> for accurate positioning. GPS provides 5-15 meter accuracy outdoors, LBS fills gaps indoors, and Wi-Fi further refines the position.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3>2. SIM Card and Network</h3>\r\n<p>In Georgia, smartwatches work with <strong>Magti</strong>, <strong>Silknet</strong>, or <strong>Cellfie</strong> Nano-SIM cards. 4G models ensure stable connectivity and support video calls. 2G models are budget-friendly but limited to voice calls and SMS.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Important:</strong> Disable the PIN code from your phone before inserting the SIM into the watch. A PIN-locked SIM will not work in the watch.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3>3. Battery Life</h3>\r\n<p>A minimum <strong>680 mAh</strong> battery lasts 2-3 days with normal use. 4G models drain faster during video calls and active GPS tracking.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3>4. Water Resistance</h3>\r\n<p><strong>IP67</strong> means the watch handles handwashing, rain, and light splashes. For swimming, IP68 is recommended.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3>5. Camera</h3>\r\n<p>A front camera is used for video calls Рђћ parents see their child in real time. Some models also support photo capture.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</section>\r\n\r\n<section>\r\n<h2>Age-Based Recommendations</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Ages 4-6 Рђћ First Watch</h3>\r\n<p>Simple interface, SOS button, and GPS are essential. Recommended: <a href=\"/products/high-quality-kids-smartwatch-q12-waterproof-ip67-2g-child-anti-lost-sos-call-gsm-lbs-location\">Q12 Рђћ 2G</a> or <a href=\"/products/children-smartwatch\">Q21 Рђћ 2G</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Ages 7-10 Рђћ Active Years</h3>\r\n<p>Camera, school mode, and geo-fence become important. Recommended: <a href=\"/products/wonlex-cheaper-kids-gps-smart-watch-4g-ct23\">Wonlex CT23 Рђћ 4G</a> or <a href=\"/products/ct27-ultra-small-4g-rtos-gps-watch\">Wonlex CT27 Рђћ Compact 4G</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Ages 11+ Рђћ Video Calls & Apps</h3>\r\n<p>Older kids need video calls and full Setracker2 app functionality. Recommended: <a href=\"/products/2024-newest-style-4g-smart-watch-sos-call-wifi-lbs-gps-tracker-android-smart-watch-kid-sos-camera-alarm-clock-kt34\">Wonlex KT34 Рђћ 4G</a> or <a href=\"/products/wonlex-kt20-4g-waterproof-smart-watch\">Wonlex KT20 Рђћ 4G Waterproof</a>.</p>\r\n</section>\r\n\r\n<section>\r\n<h2>Wonlex vs YQT Рђћ Brand Comparison</h2>\r\n<p><strong>Wonlex</strong> Рђћ premium segment: high-quality display, stable 4G connectivity. <strong>YQT</strong> Рђћ best price-to-quality ratio, wide range from 2G to 4G.</p>\r\n</section>\r\n\r\n<section>\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p>When choosing a kids smartwatch, focus on GPS accuracy, SIM compatibility with Georgian carriers, and age-appropriate features. <a href=\"/products\">Browse MyTechnic\'s full catalog</a> and find the ideal model for your child.</p>\r\n</section>','рЃарЃЮрЃЏрЃћрЃџрЃў рЃАрЃЏрЃљрЃарЃб рЃАрЃљрЃљрЃЌрЃў рЃљрЃЋрЃўрЃарЃЕрЃўрЃЮрЃЌ рЃЉрЃљрЃЋрЃерЃЋрЃўрЃАрЃЌрЃЋрЃўрЃА 2026 Рђћ рЃАрЃарЃБрЃџрЃў рЃАрЃљрЃ«рЃћрЃџрЃЏрЃФрЃдрЃЋрЃљрЃюрЃћрЃџрЃЮ | MyTechnic','Which Smartwatch to Choose for Kids 2026 Рђћ Complete Guide | MyTechnic','GPS, SIM, рЃЎрЃљрЃЏрЃћрЃарЃљ, рЃЉрЃљрЃбрЃљрЃарЃћрЃљ Рђћ рЃЉрЃљрЃЋрЃерЃЋрЃўрЃА рЃАрЃЏрЃљрЃарЃб рЃАрЃљрЃљрЃЌрЃўрЃА рЃљрЃарЃЕрЃћрЃЋрЃўрЃА рЃАрЃарЃБрЃџрЃў рЃАрЃљрЃ«рЃћрЃџрЃЏрЃФрЃдрЃЋрЃљрЃюрЃћрЃџрЃЮ 2026. рЃљрЃАрЃљрЃЎрЃЮрЃЉрЃарЃўрЃЋрЃў рЃарЃћрЃЎрЃЮрЃЏрЃћрЃюрЃЊрЃљрЃфрЃўрЃћрЃЉрЃў рЃЊрЃљ 